Gradient Descent × Ukiyo-e
Why this scores high: Hokusai's diagonal compositions + a figure descending a mountain = structurally perfect. The tradition is unmistakable and the concept is visually embedded.
Ideogram Prompt:
Katsushika Hokusai ukiyo-e woodblock print style. A lone 
traveler descends a steep mountain path through layered mist, 
each footstep carefully placed on the slope below. Multiple 
valleys visible in the distance at different depths. Flat 
unmodulated areas of indigo, ochre, and ivory. Bold black 
outlines. Visible woodgrain texture in the sky. Strong 
diagonal composition from top-right to bottom-left. Mount 
Fuji visible in far background. Edo period Japanese aesthetic, 
1830s. No text, no labels, no photographs, no shading gradients.
Negative prompt: photographic shading, 3D rendering, Western perspective, text, labels, gradients, modern elements, anime